The chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC) Caretaker/Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC), Governor Mai Mala Buni, on Thursday, met with the acting chairman of the committee, Governor Abubakar Sani Bello, and other members of the committee. Buni returned to Nigeria on Wednesday night after a medical trip to UAE and a stop-over meeting with President Muhammadu Buhari in London over the leadership crisis rocking the party. The meeting with the CECPC members, which took place at Yobe State Governors’ Lodge in Asokoro, Abuja, attracted all members of the caretaker except the Secretary, Senator John Akpanudoedehe. It was also gathered the Yobe State governor met with chairman of the Progressive Governors Forum (PGF), Governor Abubakar Atiku Bagudu, where he was briefed on the outcome of the forum’s meeting on Wednesday night. Details Later…